              <p>The visibility of text drops to zero to the immediate left of the "a-" of "air",
                meaning that this might be the ending of a longer word (three syllables maximum)
                rather than the preposition <hi rend="italics">air</hi>. In fact, lines ab, as now
                visible, are missing one of the two required perfect internal rhymes, and a word
                ending in "-uair" (: "buain") would supply such a rhyme. Nothing more can be said
                about this hypothesised word, unfortunately.</p>
            </note>
